A RESOLUTION
1 Commending the Building Owners and Managers Association of Georgia (BOMA Georgia)
2 and recognizing February 4, 2025, as BOMA Georgia Day at the state capitol; and for other
3 purposes.
4 WHEREAS, founded in 1913 as BOMA-Atlanta, BOMA Georgia is a trade association that
5 has supported the commercial real estate industry in Georgia for 112 years; and
6 WHEREAS, the commercial real estate industry has grown to currently contribute nearly
7 $5.5 billion to Georgia's economy annually while supporting nearly 50,000 jobs in the state;
8 and
9 WHEREAS, BOMA Georgia members are responsible for the ownership, management, and
10 administration of more than 150 million square feet of office space and additional millions
11 of square feet of facilities throughout Georgia; and
12 WHEREAS, these individuals represent building ownership, professional property
13 management firms, professional service providers, and contract services across more than
14 40 other categories of specialty services, and BOMA Georgia members have been
