15 instrumental in cementing Georgia as a national leader in commercial real estate over the past
16 century; and
17 WHEREAS, in 2014, BOMA Georgia established the BOMA Georgia Foundation, a
18 charitable organization contributing to research and education in the commercial real estate
19 industry that has increased support of the State of Georgia's role as a cutting-edge leader in
20 commercial real estate and business initiatives for nearly a decade; and
21 WHEREAS, BOMA Georgia has been recognized nationally for excellence in diversity and
22 inclusion; environmental sustainability; education; volunteerism; corporate responsibility;
23 and more across its 112-year lifespan; and
24 WHEREAS, it is abundantly fitting and proper that the outstanding accomplishments and
25 history of this extraordinary organization be recognized.
26 NOW, THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED BY THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES that
27 the members of this body commend the Building Owners and Managers Association of
28 Georgia upon its 112th anniversary and recognize February 4, 2025, as BOMA Georgia Day
29 at the state capitol.
30 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that the Clerk of the House of Representatives is authorized
31 and directed to make an appropriate copy of this resolution available for distribution to the
32 Building Owners and Managers Association of Georgia.
